FBIS4-18751 "drweu069_b_94013" FBIS-WEU-94-069 Daily Report 10 Apr 1994 BENELUX COUNTRIES Belgium Red Cross To Fly Medical Supplies to Kigali Red Cross To Fly Medical Supplies to Kigali AU1104085394 Paris AFP in English 2339 GMT 10 Apr 94 AU1104085394 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Brussels, April 11 (AFP) -- Two surgical teams were to fly out for Kigali on Monday [11 April], the Belgian Red Cross said Sunday. The two surgical teams, one from the Belgian Red Cross and the other from the International Committee of the Red Cross were to be flown aboard a specially chartered Boeing 707, initially to the Red Cross logistical base in Bujumbura, the capital of neighbouring Burundi. From there, the teams and medical equipment would be taken by road to Kigali where four days of ethnic violence between Hutus and Tutsis has claimed at least 1,000 lives.
